leadership_approach|process_results_people_vision|narrowing_1|1|Organised before owned|The route may become clear before enough shared ownership has formed. People may know what to do, but still feel the plan belongs more to you than to the group, which can weaken commitment later.|people|review|leadership_approach::process_results_people_vision::narrowing_1
leadership_approach|process_results_people_vision|narrowing_2|2|Pressure narrows participation|Under pressure, you may involve fewer people and move quickly into correction or action. That can restore order quickly, but it can also create distance if people feel managed through the pressure rather than brought with you through it.|people|review|leadership_approach::process_results_people_vision::narrowing_2
leadership_approach|process_results_people_vision|narrowing_3|3|Short-term route, under-explained purpose|The pattern can narrow when structure and delivery become the only trusted route. You may solve the immediate issue while leaving the wider direction under-explained, so the team follows the plan without fully seeing what it is meant to build.|vision|review|leadership_approach::process_results_people_vision::narrowing_3
